        <para id="id17011113"> BRAIN-TEASER!</para>
        <para id="id14583085">Find the following factors (you may use your calculator, if necessary):</para>
        <para id="id15395261">a) 3 786   </para>
        <para id="id16845649">____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id16845653">____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id15532748">____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id17011075"/>
        <para id="id16928151">b) 8 742   </para>
        <para id="id14444963">____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id14444969">____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id16448623">____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id4394175">1.4 Compete with a friend to see whose answers are written down first:</para>
        <para id="id16887652">9 x 7 = 7 x__________________</para>
        <para id="id10247100">716 x 18 = __________________</para>
        <para id="id14262985">__________________ v 16 = 16 x 15 </para>
        <para id="id11346586">18 x 716 = 12 888</para>
        <para id="id3497332">324 x __________________ = 18 x 324 </para>
        <para id="id16780014">563 v 347 = 195 361</para>
        <para id="id16593676">1 476 x 326 = 326 x__________________</para>
        <para id="id14481869">347 x 536 = __________________</para>
        <list id="id17023954" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>What do you realise?   </item>
        </list>
        <para id="id16440959"/>
        <para id="id16712376">DID YOU KNOW?</para>
        <para id="id4252540">We call the above the <emphasis effect="bold">COMMUTATIVE PROPERTY</emphasis> of multiplication.</para>
        <para id="id10658978">DID YOU ALSO KNOW?</para>
        <para id="id17160816">The <emphasis effect="bold">ASSOCIATIVE PROPERTY</emphasis> of multiplication looks like this:</para>
        <para id="id10672228">(6 x 5) x 2 = 6 x (2 x 5)</para>
        <para id="id14366463">2 x (3 x 4) = (2 x 3) x 4</para>
        <para id="id14418810">Thus, it makes no difference how we <emphasis effect="bold">GROUP</emphasis> the numbers because the answer stays the same.</para>
